item.description:
@SandScape wrote:

aye go to player.java and umm
search for this

// initial x and y coordinates of the player

then you see this


		// initial x and y coordinates of the player
		heightLevel = 0;
		// the first call to updateThisPlayerMovement() will craft the proper
		// initialization packet
		toX = ****+misc.random(3);
		toY = ****+misc.random(3);

those *s are the numbers of the cords i just took the numbers out to show you, and change them to any cord you want
